--- USW_TS3_TS4 ---

Umbrella-sampling stage connecting TS3 and TS4 (see ../README), seeded from
../SMD_TS3_TS4/<rep>/lmp_files/ and restrained on 'coelp'. Structurally identical in layout
to LFER_3_mg2/pph4/PMF_react_TS1/USW_100_react_TS1/: 100 window subfolders per replica
('000'-'099'), each with a static harmonic restraint (KAPPA=300 kcal/mol/A^2) centered on its
own coelp value spanning 1.9-2.7 in even steps ('generate_US_window.py' builds the windows
and the matching 'plumed_USW_<NNN>.dat' files); 'inputs/lmp_files/' is the traceability copy
of the seed structures; 'WHAM/' holds the per-replica WHAM reconstruction ('input.txt',
'job_wham.sh', the resulting free-energy profile 'fepTS3_TS4_pph4.out' and diagnostic plots) —
see PMF_react_TS1/USW_100_react_TS1/README for the full per-window/WHAM file description,
substituting the coordinate name.

Unlike the reactant-side USW_100_* folders, this folder additionally carries a top-level
'average_PMF.py': it loads the three replicas' 'fepTS3_TS4_pph4.out' profiles, averages them
point-by-point (skipping non-finite bins), writes the result to 'average_pmf_noerror.dat', and
plots it to 'average_pmf.png' with per-point error bars (std. dev. across replicas) and an
annotated arrow marking the TS3->TS4 free-energy gap between the global minimum and the
relative minimum along the profile.

Three replicas (rep1/2/3) — one README covers all three.

Note: this README documents pre-existing content; no existing file was modified.
